Document: RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration
Path: godot/classes/class_renderscenebuffersconfiguration.rst
Summary: Describes the RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration object, which is used to configure RenderSceneBuffers.

RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration is a configuration object created and populated by the render engine on a viewport change. It is used to reconfigure a RenderSceneBuffers object.
---CHUNK---
Document: RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration
Path: godot/classes/class_renderscenebuffersconfiguration.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for configuring render scene buffers, including anisotropic filtering, FSR sharpness, internal and target sizes, MSAA, render targets, scaling mode, screen space AA, mipmap bias, and view count.

Properties:
* anisotropic_filtering_level (ViewportAnisotropicFiltering): Controls the level of anisotropic filtering applied. Default: 2.
* fsr_sharpness (float): Controls the sharpness of the FidelityFX Super Resolution (FSR) upscaling. Default: 0.0.
* internal_size (Vector2i): The internal resolution used for rendering before upscaling. Default: Vector2i(0, 0).
* msaa_3d (ViewportMSAA): The Multi-Sample Anti-Aliasing (MSAA) mode for 3D rendering. Default: 0.
* render_target (RID): The RID of the render target to use. Default: RID().
* scaling_3d_mode (ViewportScaling3DMode): The mode for 3D viewport scaling. Default: 255.
* screen_space_aa (ViewportScreenSpaceAA): The screen-space anti-aliasing mode. Default: 0.
* target_size (Vector2i): The final resolution of the rendered output. Default: Vector2i(0, 0).
* texture_mipmap_bias (float): Bias applied to texture mipmap levels. Default: 0.0.
* view_count (int): The number of views to render. Default: 1.
---CHUNK---
Document: RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration
Path: godot/classes/class_renderscenebuffersconfiguration.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of the RenderSceneBuffersConfiguration class, which control various rendering buffer settings.

Property: anisotropic_filtering_level (ViewportAnisotropicFiltering)
Description: Level of the anisotropic filter.
Default: 2
Method: set_anisotropic_filtering_level(value: ViewportAnisotropicFiltering)
Method: get_anisotropic_filtering_level() -> ViewportAnisotropicFiltering

Property: fsr_sharpness (float)
Description: FSR Sharpness applicable if FSR upscaling is used.
Default: 0.0
Method: set_fsr_sharpness(value: float)
Method: get_fsr_sharpness() -> float

Property: internal_size (Vector2i)
Description: The size of the 3D render buffer used for rendering.
Default: Vector2i(0, 0)
Method: set_internal_size(value: Vector2i)
Method: get_internal_size() -> Vector2i

Property: msaa_3d (ViewportMSAA)
Description: The MSAA mode we're using for 3D rendering.
Default: 0
Method: set_msaa_3d(value: ViewportMSAA)
Method: get_msaa_3d() -> ViewportMSAA

Property: render_target (RID)
Description: The render target associated with these buffer.
Default: RID()
Method: set_render_target(value: RID)
Method: get_render_target() -> RID

Property: scaling_3d_mode (ViewportScaling3DMode)
Description: The requested scaling mode with which we upscale/downscale if internal_size and target_size are not equal.
Default: 255
Method: set_scaling_3d_mode(value: ViewportScaling3DMode)
Method: get_scaling_3d_mode() -> ViewportScaling3DMode

Property: screen_space_aa (ViewportScreenSpaceAA)
Description: The requested screen space AA applied in post processing.
Default: 0
Method: set_screen_space_aa(value: ViewportScreenSpaceAA)
Method: get_screen_space_aa() -> ViewportScreenSpaceAA

Property: target_size (Vector2i)
Description: The target (upscale) size if scaling is used.
Default: Vector2i(0, 0)
Method: set_target_size(value: Vector2i)
Method: get_target_size() -> Vector2i

Property: texture_mipmap_bias (float)
Description: Bias applied to mipmaps.
Default: 0.0
Method: set_texture_mipmap_bias(value: float)
Method: get_texture_mipmap_bias() -> float

Property: view_count (int)
Description: The number of views we're rendering.
Default: 1
Method: set_view_count(value: int)
Method: get_view_count() -> int